    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute> <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> - 88.</dateline></opener>
                <p>Do not despair about the prints of <placeName ref="pl1202">spanish</placeName> illustrious: for I shall write to 
                    <persName ref="pe0065">my son</persName> to get them at <placeName ref="pl1023">Paris</placeName> if done by any 
                    <placeName ref="pl0925">french</placeName> artists.</p>
                <p>I have <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="7" reason="illegible"/></del> scarcely <add place="above">any</add>
                    sort of trouble to give except on y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> own account. Please to return the sheets 
                    you have of the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0025">arctic zoology</title></bibl> in order to have the additions 
                    <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/></del> I discovered. If I must trouble you let it be to get 
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0625"><persName ref="pe0902">Paterson</persName>'s acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> of the <placeName ref="pl1480">cape of Good Hope</placeName></title></bibl>
                    &amp; add it to y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Parcel: Please to get it from <persName ref="pe0327">m<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Robson</persName>.
                    I am now sailing by
                    <lb/><placeName ref="pl1481">Mombaza</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="pl1482">Quiloa</placeName>, &amp; <placeName ref="pl1483">melind</placeName>
                    <lb/>And <placeName ref="pl1484">Sofala</placeName>, thought <placeName ref="pl1485">ophir</placeName>.<note type="editorial">Pennant quotes from John Milton, <hi rend="italic">Paradise Lost</hi>, XI, lines 399â€“400.</note>
                    <lb/>But trust we shall meet in the Port of <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName> in December.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Adieu
                    <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> most truely</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Th. Pennant</persName></signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
